{"questionId":"9082915","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Show that, when the speed of the train is 10 m s-1, the frequency of the periodic force is 0.4 Hz.</span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">time period </span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">T = «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{25}{10}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>25</mn>\n    <mn>10</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>» </span></em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">= 2.5 s</span><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">&nbsp;<strong>AND</strong> f = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{T}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></span></em></p>\n<p><strong><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">OR</span></em></strong></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">evidence of f&nbsp;= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{10}{25}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>10</mn>\n    <mn>25</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>✔</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Answer 0.4 Hz is given, check correct working is shown.</span></span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9082915","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.a","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Show that, when the speed of the train is 10 m s-1, the frequency of the periodic force is 0.4 Hz.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["C. Wave behaviour","C.4 Standing waves and resonance"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}